                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d897">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/2618</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Persian Minister</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MK1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mehdi Khan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 3, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: [I beg to acknowledge the receipt of your note of
                    December 17, in which you state that the Persian Government advised you by cable
                    to seek officially the assistance of the United States Government in securing
                    for Persia representation in the peace conference which will convene at the
                    termination of this great war, and also to assist Persia to maintain the rights
                    belonging to her as independent and sovereign state.</p>
                <p>Your note has been read with great interest and deep sympathy and the requests
                    contained therein are being very carefully studied by officials of the
                    Department. The magnitude of the problems involved has precluded a hasty answer
                    to the questions contained in your note. It is hoped, however, that it will be
                    possible to reply to your note in the very near future.]</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
